Summary of Today’s Work
Task 1: Producer-Consumer Problem with Pipes
Blocking pipes mein issue nahi hota—Producer har 1 second mein bhejta, Consumer har 3 seconds mein padhta.
Task 2: Merge Sort with Multiple Processes
3 child processes array ka 1/3rd part sort karte the, parent merge karta tha.
Tu ne kaha sorting nahi chahiye.
Task 3: Simplified Array Splitting with Pipes
2 child processes array ka hissa pipe se bhejte the, parent print karta tha.
Task 4: Chat Application Between Two Processes
Parent aur child pipes se chat karte the, "bye" pe rukta tha.
Task 5: Monitor Child Processes with Pipes
3 child processes banaye, start aur end times pipe se collect kiye, most CPU-bound process bataya.
Task 6: Random Numbers
rand() aur <random> se random numbers banaye.
Task 7: Creation of n*n Matrix
Dynamic memory se n*n matrix banaya, random numbers se fill kiya.
Task 8: Matrix Multiplication with Child Processes
2 n*n matrices banaye, file mein save kiye.
n child processes banaye—har child ne ek row ka multiplication kiya, result file mein save kiya.
Task 9 (Current): Matrix Multiplication with n Processes (Custom n Calculation)
n calculate kiya using random number, roll number, aur conditions.
2 matrices banaye, file mein save kiye.
Change: Pointers (int** matrix) ki jagah VLA (int matrix[genNum][genNum]) use kiya kyunki tu ne kaha pointers mushkil hain.
n child processes banaye, har child ne ek row ka multiplication kiya, result file mein save kiya.
Parent ne saare results read karke final matrix print kiya.
Final Notes
VLA Use Kiya: Pointers hata kar int matrix1[genNum][genNum] use kiya taake simple rahe.
Matrix Multiplication: Har child ne ek row ka result calculate kiya, file mein save kiya.
Parent: Saare results ko read karke final matrix print kiya.
Yaad Rakh: Agar VLA kaam na kare (compiler error de), to bol dena, hum pointers wapas use karenge.
